<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-83-0396 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper outlines the evaluation process of deriving heat transfer coefficientsfrom measured data in the cold leg by virtue of an iterative one-dimensionalmethod and demonstrates this assessment for a representative experiment.The evaluated heat transfer coefficients of all TEMB experiments arepresented in terms of Nu-numbers as compared to the well-known semi-empiricalcorrelation by Hausen in order to assess the validity of this generalcorrelation for the specific PTS-requirements. (orig./HP)</TEXT></DOC>